# TypeScript Patterns

## Types

- Core interfaces in `src/types.ts`: `NewsArticle`, `NewsCategory`, `Sentiment`, `SentimentDisplay`
- Error types in `src/types/errors.ts`: discriminated union `AppError` with `type` field
- Use `interface` for object shapes, `type` for unions and aliases

## Services

Services return result objects, never throw:

```typescript
// Good: explicit result type
interface ServiceResult {
  data: Data
  error: AppError | null
}

// Bad: throwing errors
throw new Error('something failed')
```

## Environment variables

- Access via `import.meta.env.VITE_*` (Vite convention)
- Only `VITE_`-prefixed vars are exposed to client code
- Defined in `.env`, documented in `.env.example`
